findings.subquery: Deepak Ghengat's contributions to his field
key_findings: Deepak Ghengat has made significant contributions in the fields of artificial intelligence (AI), machine learning (ML), and bioinformatics, focusing on algorithm development, pattern discovery, and data mining techniques.
He has co-authored research papers on topics such as the Improved Edmonds-Karp Algorithm for network flow problems and efficient algorithm design for pattern discovery in bioinformatics sequences.
Ghengat has also worked on algorithms for content distribution in networks and comparative analyses of various approaches used in frequent pattern mining.
His research has been published in reputable journals and conferences, contributing to advancements in computational intelligence and data analysis.

Additionally, Ghengat has been involved in collaborative projects aimed at mainstreaming AI and ML skills in India, including a project funded by the Royal Academy of Engineering in partnership with several universities and industry partners.
He has also been involved in projects related to toxicity assessment and hardware security, demonstrating a broad application of his expertise in AI and ML.
